section.section:
Except as provided in § 8-715(d) of this subtitle and in subsections (e) and (f) of this section, and in addition to the fees prescribed in subsection (b) of this section, an excise tax is levied at the rate of 5% of the fair market value of the vessel on:
The issuance of every original certificate of title required for a vessel under this subtitle;
The issuance of every subsequent certificate of title for the sale, resale, or transfer of the vessel;
The sale within the State of every other vessel; and
The possession within the State of a vessel used or to be used principally in the State.

text.section:
A person is not required to pay the tax provided for in subsection (c) of this section resulting from:
A transfer between members of the immediate family as determined by Department regulations;
A transfer between members of the immediate family as determined by Department regulations of a documented vessel for which the transferor applied for and was issued a valid use sticker under § 8-712.1 of this subtitle;
A transfer to a licensed dealer of a vessel for resale, rental, or leasing purposes;
The holding of a vessel that is titled or numbered in another state or is federally documented, provided:
The vessel is held for resale or listed for resale by a licensed dealer; and
The vessel owner signs an affidavit that there will be no use of the vessel on the waters of the State other than for a sea trial;
Purchase of a vessel by the State or any political subdivision;
Purchase of a vessel by an eleemosynary organization which the Secretary has approved;
The purchase within the State of a vessel if the owner paid or incurred a liability for the Maryland sales and use tax on the vessel prior to July 1, 1986;
The possession within the State of a vessel which was purchased outside the State if the owner paid or incurred a liability for the Maryland use tax on the vessel prior to July 1, 1986;
The possession of a vessel in the State that is not used or to be used principally on the waters of the State and for which the issuance of a title is not sought or required under this subtitle, except that:
A vessel is not deemed used on the waters of the State if the vessel is used for 90 days or less of a calendar year; and
If a vessel is used for more days than 90 days in a calendar year, the period of 90 days shall be counted in the determination of principal use under this subtitle;
The possession within the State of a vessel if the current owner, before July 1, 1986:
The possession within the State of a vessel that:
Is owned by a nonprofit organization that:
Is used for the purposes of the organization;
The possession within the State of a vessel for a period of not more than one year if the current owner is a member of the armed services and is serving on active duty in this State; or
The sale of a vessel within the State if:
The vessel is purchased from a licensed dealer;
The issuance of a title is not sought or required;
The vessel is not used or to be used principally on the waters of this State;
The vessel is duly registered in another jurisdiction within 30 days of the date of purchase; and
The dealer and the purchaser execute an agreement certifying the state of principal use for the vessel which is filed with the Department within 30 days of the date of purchase.
